# Architecture & Standards (Azure DevOps AI PR Reviewer)

## Goals

- Produce **high-signal, deterministic** review output (structured findings → publishable comment threads).
- Keep the AI layer **pluggable** (CodeRabbit preferred, LLM fallback) behind a stable interface.
- Ensure **secrets are server-only** (Azure DevOps PATs, encryption keys never reach the browser).
- Keep **UI thin**; put business logic in a **domain/review pipeline**.

## Layering & boundaries

- **UI layer** (Next.js App Router): pages/layouts/forms/preview.
- **Server boundary** (Route Handlers / Server Actions): validate input → call use-case → return DTOs.
- **Domain layer** (`server/review`): orchestrates review pipeline; no UI concerns.
- **Integrations**:
  - Azure DevOps adapter (`server/azure-devops`) via `azure-devops-node-api`
  - Git adapter (`server/git`) for local clone/fetch + unified diffs (`git diff ...` via `execa`)
  - AI engines (`server/ai`) normalize engine output → structured findings
- **Persistence** (`server/db` + `prisma/`): Prisma models for settings/standards/runs/findings/publish history.

**Hard rule**: server-only modules live under `server/` and must not be imported by Client Components.
Add `import "server-only";` to server-only modules as a guardrail.

## Repository structure (target)

- `app/`: routes, layouts, route handlers (`app/api/**/route.ts`), route-scoped UI in `app/**/_components/`
- `components/`: shared React components; `components/ui/` reserved for shadcn/ui
- `lib/`: shared utilities (config/env parsing, validation schemas, crypto helpers, pure utils)
- `server/`: server-only domain + integrations (azure-devops/git/ai/review/db)
- `prisma/`: schema + migrations
- `scripts/`: maintenance/one-off scripts

## Conventions & best practices

- **Naming**: folders/routes/files in `kebab-case`; React exports in `PascalCase`; values/functions in `camelCase`.
- **Validation**: validate at boundaries (requests, persistence, AI output). Prefer `unknown` + Zod over `any`.
- **Error handling**: use typed domain errors; never swallow external errors; surface safe summaries at the edge.
- **Security**: encrypt PATs at rest (AES-256-GCM using `APP_ENCRYPTION_KEY`); never log or send secrets to client.
- **Logging**: structured, event-focused logs; avoid logging raw diffs by default.
- **Quality**: keep ESLint/Prettier on; don’t disable rules without a documented reason.
